elements.description:
`cosmoz-omnitable-treenode-column`
cosmoz-omnitable column to display a tree node

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: If the column should be disabled until enabled with enabledColumns

properties.name: editable
properties.description: If true, the column will be editable by using an input element for rendering.

properties.name: externalValues
properties.description: Values to filter this column will be managed outside of omnitable

properties.name: headerFocused
properties.description:
Indicates whether the user has engaged with the
header/filter component of the column

properties.name: loading
properties.description: Indicate that the column is loading/performing work

properties.name: bindValues
properties.description: Ask for a list of values

properties.name: name
properties.description: Column name for use with enabledColumns

properties.name: isOmnitableColumn
properties.description:
Used to indicate that an element using this behavior is a column definition that can be used
in cosmoz-omnitable

properties.name: editWidth
properties.description: Base width of this column when in edit mode.

properties.name: flex
properties.description: Width growing factor for this column.

properties.name: overflow
properties.description:
Allow column to overflow without triggering
column folding (good for long descriptions)

properties.name: columnIndex
properties.description: Index of this column in the list of displayed columns (excluding disabled/hidden columns).

properties.name: showCommonPath
properties.description:
If displayed node share a common path from root, this property indicates wether this common
path should be replaced by an ellipsis.

properties.name: keyProperty
properties.description: Name of the property used to lookup the displayed node in the tree

properties.name: queryFn
properties.description:
Function used to filter available items.
This function is actually used by `paper-autocomplete`,
it is also exposed here so it is possible to provide a custom queryFn.

methods.name: hasFilter
methods.description: Returns whether `filterNotify.base` or `filter` is set to a usable value.

return.desc: True if filter or filterNotify.base is set

methods.name: getPathByProperty
methods.description: HACK(pasleq): Cosmoz.Tree API needs to be fixed to avoid such code in components
